sentences:
Kumar Sekhar Kammula ( ) is an Indian film director , screenwriter and producer , known for his works exclusively in Telugu cinema .
A Master of Fine Arts Holder from Howard University , he made his directorial debut with the independent film Dollar Dreams ( 2000 ) , which was a critical success , and won him the National Film Award for Best First film of a director .
The film was screened at the International Film Festival of India .
Sekhar has garnered two filmfare Awards South , and six state Nandi Awards for his works .
Sekhar was among the director 's delegation to represent Indian Cinema at the 2011 Cannes Film Festival .
His second film , Anand , was a blockbuster in 2004 .
His next film , Godavari , was praised by critics and was a hit .
Happy Days , which was released on 28 September 2007 , was declared a smash hit .
It was remade in Tamil and Kannada .
He was a writer for Tamil version which was released in 2010 .
He then directed Leader released on 19 February 2010 to positive reviews .
In 2016 , Sekhar Kammula announced his Bollywood debut with a film starring Salman Khan .
